ive%20moat%20around%20their%20economic%20castles.%20The%20average%20company%2C%20in%20contrast%2C%20does%20battle%20daily%20without%20any%20such%20means%20of%20protection.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Berkshire%20CEO%20built%20on%20the%20idea%20in%20his%202007%20letter%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BA%20truly%20great%20business%20must%20have%20an%20enduring%20'moat'%20that%20protects%20excellent%20returns%20on%20invested%20capital.%20The%20dynamics%20of%20capitalism%20guarantee%20that%20competitors%20will%20repeatedly%20assault%20any%20business%20'castle'%20that%20is%20earning%20high%20returns.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETherefore%20a%20formidable%20barrier%20such%20as%20a%20company's%20being%20the%20low-cost%20producer%20(GEICO%2C%20Costco)%20or%20possessing%20a%20powerful%20worldwide%20brand%20(Coca-Cola%2C%20Gillette%2C%20American%20Express)%20is%20essential%20for%20sustained%20success.%20Business%20history%20is%20filled%20with%20'Roman%20Candles%2C'%20companies%20whose%20moats%20proved%20illusory%20and%20were%20soon%20crossed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20billionaire%20deployed%20the%20metaphor%20once%20again%20during%20Berkshire's%202017%20meeting%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you've%20got%20a%20wonderful%20business%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20a%20small%20one%20like%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarren-buffett-berkshire-hathaway-dream-business-is-sees-candies-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESee's%20Candy%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20you%20basically%20have%20an%20economic%20castle.%20And%20in%20capitalism%2C%20people%20are%20going%20to%20try%20and%20take%20away%20that%20castle%20from%20you.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESo%2C%20you%20want%20a%20moat%20around%20it%20that%20can%20protect%20it.%20And%20then%20you%20want%20a%20knight%20in%20the%20castle%20that's%20pretty%20darn%20good%20at%20warding%20off%20marauders.%