0slow%20down%2C%20buying%20time%20to%20clear%20the%20bridge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20did%20the%20Baltimore%20bridge%20collapse%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%201%20a.m.%20EDT%20(0500%20GMT)%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20a%20container%20ship%20named%20the%20Dali%20was%20sailing%20down%20the%20Patapsco%20River%20on%20its%20way%20to%20Sri%20Lanka.%20At%201%3A24%20a.m.%2C%20it%20suffered%20a%20total%20power%20failure%20and%20all%20its%20lights%20went%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20minutes%20later%2C%20at%201%3A27%20a.m.%2C%20the%20container%20ship%20struck%20a%20pylon%20of%20the%20bridge%2C%20crumpling%20almost%20the%20entire%20structure%20into%20the%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELess%20than%20a%20minute%20before%20impact%2C%20a%20first%20responder%20on%20emergency%20radio%20responded%20to%20the%20crew's%20mayday%20call%20by%20sending%20officers%20to%20halt%20traffic%20onto%20the%20bridge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20their%20fast%20work%2C%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20disaster%20may%20have%20been%20far%20greater%2C%20even%20during%20the%20early%20morning%20hours%20when%20vehicular%20traffic%20is%20relatively%20light.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETuesday's%20disaster%20may%20be%20the%20worst%20U.S.%20bridge%20collapse%20since%202007%2C%20when%20a%20design%20error%20caused%20the%20I-35W%20bridge%20in%20Minneapolis%20to%20plunge%20into%20the%20Mississippi%20River%2C%20killing%2013%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20did%20the%20bridge%20collapse%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBridges%20such%20as%20the%20one%20in%20Baltimore%20are%20classified%20as%20%26quot%3Bfracture%20critical%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20federal%20government%20-%20meaning%20that%20if%20one%20portion%20of%20the%20bridge%20collapses%2C%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20structure%20falls.%20There%20are%20more%20than%2016%2C800%20such%20spans%20in%20the%20U.S.%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Federal%20Highway%20Administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20head%20of%20the%20National%20Transportation%20Safety%20Board%20said%20the%20bridge%20lacked%20structural%20engineering%20redundancies%20common%20to%20newer%20spans%2C%20making%20it%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20catastrophic%20collapse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Key%20Bridge%20opened%20in%201977%20-%20three%20years%20before%20a%20similar%20vessel%20collision%20of%20the%20Sunshine%20Skyway%20Bridge%20in%20Tampa%20Bay%2C%20Florida%2C%20killed%2035%20people%2C%20and%20prompted%20bridge%20designers%20to%20implement%20better%20protections%20for%20foundation%20piers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20will%20pay%20for%20the%20damage%20and%20how%20much%20will%20it%20cost%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden%20promised%20to%20visit%20Baltimore%20soon%20and%20said%20he%20wanted%20the%20federal%20government%20to%20pay%20to%20rebuild%20the%20bridge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Transportation%20Department%20on%20Thursday%20awarded%20%2460%20million%20in%20%26quot%3Bquick%20release%26quot%3B%20emergency%20relief%20funds%20to%20aid%20in%20clearing%20debris%20and%20begin%20the%20process%20of%20rebuilding.%20To%20replace%20the%20bridge%2C%20Congress%20would%20need%20to%20approve%20funding.%20After%20the%20bridge%20collapse%20in%202007%20in%20Minnesota%2C%20Congress%20allocated%20%24250%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitial%20estimates%20put%20the%20cost%20of%20rebuilding%20the%20bridge%20at%20%24600%20million%2C%20according%20to%20economic%20analysis%20company%20IMPLAN.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFederal%20officials%20have%20told%20Maryland%20lawmakers%20the%20final%20cost%20of%20rebuilding%20the%20bridge%20could%20soar%20to%20at%20least%20%242%20billion%2C%20Roll%20Call%20reported%2C%20citing%20a%20source%20familiar%20with%20the%20discussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInsurers%20could%20face%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20claims%2C%20analysts%20said%2C%20with%20one%20putting%20the%20cost%20at%20as%20much%20as%20%244%20billion%2C%20which%20would%20make%20the%20tragedy%20a%20record%20shipping%20insurance%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20long%20will%20it%20take%20to%20rebuild%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERebuilding%20could%20be%20a%20lengthy%20process%20and%20will%20depend%20on%20whether%20any%20of%20the%20remaining%20structure%20can%20be%20salvaged.%20It%20took%20five%20years%20to%20construct%20the%20original%20bridge%20from%201972-1977.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20closure%20of%20the%20port%20for%20just%20one%20month%20would%20cost%20Maryland%20%2428%20million%20in%20lost%20business%2C%20according%20to%20IMPLAN.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWwhat%20ship%20hit%20the%20Baltimore%20Bridge%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Dali%20was%20leaving%20Baltimore%20en%20route%20to%20Colombo%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20with%2021%20crew%20and%20two%20pilots%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ship%20measures%20948%20feet%20(289%20m)%20-%20as%20long%20as%20three%20football%20fields.%20It%20was%20stacked%20high%20with%20containers%20but%20was%20capable%20of%20carrying%20twice%20as%20much%20cargo.%20Safety%20investigators%20recovered%20the%20ship's%20black%20box%2C%20which%20can%20give%20them%20the%20vessel's%20position%2C%20speed%2C%20heading%2C%20radar%2C%20bridge%20audio%2C%20and%20radio%20communications%20as%20well%20as%20alarms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20ship%20was%20involved%20in%20an%20incident%20in%20the%20port%20of%20Antwerp%2C%20Belgium%2C%20in%202016%2C%20when%20it%20hit%20a%20quay%20as%20it%20tried%20to%20exit%20the%20North%20Sea%20container%20terminal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20later%20inspection%20in%20June%202023%20carried%20out%20in%20San%20Antonio%2C%20Chile%2C%20found%20the%20vessel%20had%20%26quot%3Bpropulsion%20and%20auxiliary%20machinery%26quot%3B%20deficiencies%2C%20according%20to%20data%20on%20the%20public%20Equasis%20website%2C%20which%20provides%20information%20on%20ships.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20registered%20owner%20of%20the%20Singapore-flagged%20ship%20is%20Grace%20Ocean%20Pte%20Ltd%2C%20LSEG%20data%20show.%20Synergy%20Marine%20Group%20managed%20the%20ship%2C%20and%20Maersk%20chartered%20the%20vessel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20do%20we%20know%20about%20the%20bridge%20that%20collapsed%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Francis%20Scott%20Key%20Bridge%20was%20one%20of%20three%20ways%20to%20cross%20the%20Baltimore%20Harbor%20and%20handled%2031%2C000%20cars%20per%20day%20or%2011.3%20million%20vehicles%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20steel%20structure%20was%20four%20lanes%20wide%20and%20rose%20185%20feet%20(56%20m)%20above%20the%20river.%C2%A0%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20opened%20in%201977%20and%20crosses%20the%20Patapsco%20River%2C%20where%20U.S.%20national%20anthem%20author%20Francis%20Scott%20Key%20wrote%20the%20%26quot%3BStar%20Spangled%20Banner%26quot%3B%20in%201814%20after%20witnessing%20the%20British%20defeat%20at%20the%20Battle%20of%20Baltimore%20and%20the%20British%20bombing%20of%20Fort%20McHenry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20will%20the%20bridge%20collapse%20impact%20the%20Baltimore%20port%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETraffic%20was%20suspended%20at%20the%20port%2C%20the%2017th%20largest%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20flow%20of%20containers%20to%20Baltimore%20can%20likely%20be%20redistributed%20to%20bigger%20ports.%20However%2C%20there%20could%20be%20major%20disruptions%20in%20shipping%20cars%2C%20coal%20and%20sugar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20the%20busiest%20U.S.%20port%20for%20car%20shipments%2C%20handling%20at%20least%20750%2C000%20vehicles%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20Maryland%20Port%20Administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20the%20port%20was%20the%20second%20busiest%20for%20coal%20exports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20the%20largest%20U.S.%20port%20by%20volume%20for%20handling%20farm%20and%20construction%20machinery%2C%20as%20well%20as%20agricultural%20products%20such%20as%20sugar%20and%20salt.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This