e%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20has%20received%20a%20Rs%201%2C800%20crore%20notice%20from%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Department%2C%20a%20day%20after%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20dismissed%20the%20party's%20petition%20challenging%20the%20tax%20notices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fresh%20notice%20is%20for%20assessment%20years%202017-18%20to%202020-21%20and%20includes%20penalty%20and%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20is%20already%20facing%20a%20funds%20crunch%20after%20Income%20Tax%20authorities%20imposed%20a%20penalty%20of%20Rs%20200%20crore%20and%20froze%20its%20funds.%20The%20party%20has%20not%20received%20any%20relief%20from%20the%20High%20Court%20in%20the%20case%20and%20is%20likely%20to%20move%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%20has%20accused%20the%20BJP%20of%20squeezing%20it%20financially%20and%20of%20using%20tax%20authorities%20against%20it%20ahead%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20beginning%20April%2019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20notices%20are%20being%20sent%20to%20cripple%20us%20financially.%20This%20is%20tax%20terrorism%2C%20and%20this%20is%20being%20used%20to%20attack%20the%20Congress%2C%20This%20has%20to%20stop%2C%26quot%3B%20Congress's%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20said%20in%20a%20press%20conference%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20asserted%20that%20the%20Congress's%20campaign%20for%20the%20upcoming%20parliamentary%20polls%20will%20continue%20and%20the%20party%20will%20take%20its%20guarantees%20to%20the%20people%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20not%20be%20scared%20of%20these%20notices.%20We%20will%20be%20more%20aggressive%20and%20fight%20these%20polls%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20Union%20minister%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20the%20I-T%20department%20had%20found%20fault%20in%20the%20party's%20tax%20returns%20and%20demanded%20Rs%20200%20crore.%20The%20Income%20Tax%20Appellate%20Tribunal%20(ITAT)%20had%20asked%20the%20party%20to%20pay%20the%20dues%20and%20froze%20their%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20said%20the%20tax%20tribunal's%20order%20freezing%20its%20funds%20was%20%26quot%3Ban%20attack%20on%20democracy%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20order%20came%20just%20ahead%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20rejected%20petitions%20by%20the%20Congress%20challenging%20the%20initiation%20of%20tax%20reassessment%20proceedings%20against%20it%20for%20a%20period%20of%20four%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFunding%20for%20political%20parties%20is%20becoming%20a%20central%20issue%20in%20this%20election%2C%20particularly%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20struck%20down%20electoral%20bonds%20-%20which%20allow%20individuals%20and%2For%20businesses%20to%20make%20anonymous%20donations%20to%20political%20parties%20-%20on%20grounds%20it%20violated%20citizens'%20right%20to%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20and%20other%20opposition%20parties%20welcomed%20the%20verdict%2C%20which%20scrapped%20a%20scheme%20that%20had%20benefitted%20the%20BJP%20the%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711704000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2F8rtbo3r8_rahul-gandhi-mallikarjun-kharge_625x300_29_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffresh-rs-1700-crore-notice-to-congress-by-income-tax-department-sources-5332367%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Congress%20has%20received%20a%20Rs%201%2C800%20crore%20notice%20from%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Department%2C%20a%20day%20after%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20dismissed%20the%20party's%20petition%20challenging%20the%20tax%20notices%2C%20according%20to%20sources.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffresh-rs-1700-crore-notice-to-congress-by-income-tax-department-sources-5332367%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffresh-rs-1700-crore-notice-to-congress-by-income-tax-department-sources-5332367%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ffresh-rs-1700-crore-notice-to-congress-by-income-tax-department-sources-5332367%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Oklahoma's%20lax%20marijuana%20laws%20made%20it%20a%20green%20utopia%20for%20the%20cannabis%20industry.%20Then%20came%20the%20mass%20murder.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Drone%20shot%20of%20a%20field%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6603a7f516bde8d4ead27c3a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22281%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EF%3C%2Fstrong%3Eourteen%20months%20after%20the%20murders%2C%20the%20garage%20of%20the%20abandoned%20marijuana%20farm%20on%20prairie%20tableland%20northwest%20of%20Oklahoma%20City%20sits%20frozen%20and%20dark.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClothes%20hangers%20meant%20for%20drying%20weed%20dangle%20from%20metal%20poles%20stretched%20across%20the%20ceiling.%20Electric%20fans%20and%20plastic%20footstools%20are%20toppled%20over.%20The%20remnants%20of%20face-high%20marijuana%20plants%20lie%20flat%20on%20the%20unswept%20concrete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElectrical%20outlets%20and%20two%20air-conditioning%20units%20are%20crudely%20cut%20into%20white%20plaster%20walls.%20Under%20one%20of%20those%20outlets%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20the%20horror%20that%20happened%20here%3A%20blood%20splatter%20dried%20to%20a%20reddish%20brown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESituated%20in%20Kingfisher%20County%2C%20Oklahoma%2C%20the%20farm%20sits%20on%20a%20dirt%20path%20about%20two%20miles%20from%20the%20nearest%20paved%20road%2C%20surrounded%20by%20flatland.%20The%20closest%20town%20is%20Ames%2C%20Oklahoma%2C%20population%20193%2C%20about%2013%20miles%20to%20the%20northwest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2020%2C%202022%2C%20a%20man%20with%20a%20handgun%20executed%20four%20people%20on%20this%20farm%2C%20inside%20this%20garage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20night%20of%20the%20murders%2C%20responding%20officers%20found%20a%20whimpering%20dog%20standing%20beside%20one%20of%20the%20bodies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20paw%20prints%20are%20still%20visible%20in%20the%20dust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20inconspicuous%20rural%20farm%20may%20have%20seemed%20like%20an%20ideal%20place%20for%20its%20owners%20to%20go%20unnoticed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20a%20mass%20murder%20hadn't%20happened%20here%2C%20it%20may%20have%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225163%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kingfisher%2C%20OK%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6601d41616bde8d4ead1f4a9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223872%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBroadway%20Avenue%20in%20Kingfisher%2C%20Oklahoma%2C%20about%2030%20miles%20south%20of%20where%20Wu%20Chen%2C%2047%2C%20executed%20four%20people%20at%20a%20marijuana%20farm.%3Cp%3EMike%20Simons%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2026%2C%202018%2C%20Oklahoma%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foklahoma-medical-cannabis-legalization-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evoters%20approved%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20by%20about%20a%2057%20percent%20margin%2C%20the%20Oklahoma%20Medical%20Marijuana%20Legalization%20Initiative%2C%20becoming%20the%2030th%20state%20in%20the%20country%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flegal-marijuana-states-2018-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegal%20cannabis%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20one%20form%20or%20another.%20But%20rules%20around%20how%20the%20state%20regulated%20it%20were%20remarkably%20spare%2C%20making%20it%20one%20of%20the%20most%20lenient%20states%20for%20growing%20and%20selling%20marijuana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Oklahoma%2C%20the%20application%20fee%20to%20start%20growing%20or%20selling%20medical%20pot%20is%20%242%2C500%2C%20and%20there%20is%20no%20statewide%20limit%20on%20the%20number%20of%20growers%20that%20can%20be%20licensed%20to%20sell%20to%20dispensaries.%20Compare%20that%20to%20Pennsylvania%2C%20where%20there's%20a%20cap%20of%2025%20marijuana%20growers%20or%20processors%20for%20the%20whole%20state%2C%20a%20nonrefundable%20%2410%2C000%20fee%20just%20to%20apply%20to%20grow%20marijuana%2C%20and%20a%20requirement%20that%20each%20licensed%20grow%20operation%20have%20access%20to%20%242%20million%20in%20capital%2C%20including%20at%20least%20%24500%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.health.pa.gov%2Ftopics%2Fprograms%2FMedical%2520Marijuana%2FPages%2FGrowers-Processors.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20bank%3C%2Fa%3E.%20California%20has%20dozens%20of%20different%20designations%20for%20types%20of%20marijuana-growing%20licenses%2C%20which%20can%20cost%20as%20much%20as%20%2477%2C905%20a%20year.%20Arkansas%2C%20next%20door%20to%20Oklahoma%2C%20has%20a%20strict%20license%20cap%20and%20restrictions%20on%20residential%20cultivation%2C%20and%20requires%20license%20holders%20to%20prove%20they%20have%20%24500%2C000%20in%20liquid%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPretty%20much%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarijuana-legalization-ballot-tracker-new-jersey-arizona-montana-vote-results-2020%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevery%20state%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20designed%20its%20own%20complicated%20set%20of%20barriers%20to%20start%20growing%20or%20selling%20marijuana%2C%20except%20Oklahoma.%20When%20Oklahoma%20legalized%20medical%20marijuana%2C%20the%20only%20real%20requirement%20was%20that%20Oklahoma%20residents%20had%20to%20be%20involved%20in%20marijuana%20growing%20and%20selling.%20Oklahoma%2C%20a%20boom-and-bust%20state%20since%20oil%20was%20first%20discovered%20there%20in%201859%2C%20exploded%20with%20marijuana%20operations.%20By%20October%202021%2C%20Oklahoma%20had%20more%20licensed%20cannabis%20farms%20than%20California%2C%20with%20a%2010th%20of%20California's%20population.%20And%20marijuana%20proved%20a%20windfall%20for%20the%20state.%20According%20to%20data%20from%20the%20Oklahoma%20Medical%20Marijuana%20Authority%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20OMMA%2C%20the%20agency%20set%20up%20to%20write%20and%20regulate%20marijuana%20policy%20in%20Oklahoma%20%E2%80%94%20the%20state%20pulled%20in%20over%20%24100%20million%20in%20tax%20revenue%20from%20marijuana%20sales%20in%202020%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20lax%20oversight%20of%20Oklahoma's%20legal%20marijuana%20market%20invited%20corruption%20and%20violence.%20Thousands%20flocked%20to%20the%20state%20seeking%20quick%20profits%20in%20cannabis%2C%20only%20to%20find%20fierce%20competition%20and%20rampant%20fraud.%20As%20criminal%20enterprises%20exploited%20the%20system's%20openness%2C%20law%20enforcement%20responded%20with%20heavy-handed%20crackdowns%2C%20gutting%20legitimate%20businesses%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Oklahoma%20voters%20had%20welcomed%20in%20the%20marijuana%20industry%2C%20its%20law-enforcement%20community%20%E2%80%94%20and%20some%20of%20the%20state's%20law-and-order%20voters%20%E2%80%94%20saw%20red.%20And%20not%20just%20because%20of%20the%20threat%20of%20violence.%20Folks%20paying%20attention%20to%20property%20records%20started%20to%20see%20lots%20of%20business%20names%20connected%20to%20investors%20from%20around%20the%20world%2C%20particularly%20Chinese%20investors.%20The%20panic%20went%20national.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202022%2C%20Oklahoma's%20Republican%20governor%2C%20Kevin%20Stitt%2C%20went%20on%20Sean%20Hannity's%20Fox%20News%20show%20to%20warn%20that%20Oklahoma%20was%20the%20state%20with%20the%20%26quot%3BNo.%201%20land%20purchases%20by%20the%20communists%20or%20foreign%20nationals%26quot%3B%20in%202020%2C%20which%20he%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20red%20flag%20for%20anybody.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20month%20later%2C%20Dan%20Newhouse%2C%20a%20Republican%20Washington%20state%20representative%2C%20wrote%20an%20op-ed%20for%20Fox%20News%20warning%20of%20%26quot%3BChinese%20nationals%20buying%20Oklahoma%20farmland%20at%20exorbitant%20prices%2C%20growing%20thousands%20of%20pounds%20of%20marijuana%2C%20and%20distributing%20it%20on%20the%20U.S.%20black%20market.%20Perhaps%20China%20considers%20this%20a%20bonus.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20quadruple%20murders%20happened.%20The%20name%20on%20the%20growing%20license%20for%20that%20farm%20in%20Kingfisher%20County%20was%20Liu%20and%20Chen%20Inc.%2C%20and%20the%20property%20was%20owned%20by%20Yi%20Fei%20Lin%2C%20a%20Chinese%20national.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfterward%2C%20people%20wondered%20why%20no%20one%20in%20law%20enforcement%20stopped%20a%20Chinese%20marijuana-growing%20operation%20where%20armed%20guards%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.enidnews.com%2Fnews%2Farmed-guards-a-fixture-outside-lacey-pot-farm-before-4-were-slain%2Farticle_41103fe6-6d09-11ed-8d07-9ff9d7e4c936.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eknown%20to%20hang%20out%20nearby%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20it%20turned%20into%20the%20site%20of%20a%20mass%20murder.%20Legalization%20was%20supposed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cato.org%2Fpolicy-analysis%2Fhow-legalizing-marijuana-securing-border-border-wall-drug-smuggling-lessons%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereduce%20the%20incentives%20for%20powerful%20cartels%20to%20sell%20marijuana%20on%20the%20black%20market%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Instead%2C%20Oklahoma%20turned%20into%20a%20playground%20for%20marijuana%20growers%20%E2%80%94%20both%20criminal%20and%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20grow%20operations%20are%20connected%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-new-york-chinatown-gangs-actually-work-crime-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20organized%20crime%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20Mark%20Woodward%2C%20a%20spokesman%20for%20the%20Oklahoma%20Bureau%20of%20Narcotics%20and%20Dangerous%20Drugs%2C%20or%20OBN%2C%20the%20law-enforcement%20entity%20that%20polices%20the%20state's%20marijuana%20industry.%20%26quot%3BThese%20farms%20are%20ultimately%20run%20by%20people%20who%20are%20tied%20to%20violent%20crime%2C%20human%20trafficking%2C%20labor%20trafficking%2C%20sex%20trafficking%2C%20homicides%2C%20extortion%2C%20money%20laundering%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20so%20many%20other%20criminal%20activities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20its%20peak%20in%202021%2C%20OBN%20received%20applications%20for%20more%20than%209%2C400%20growing%20operations.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20Oklahoma%20legislature%20set%20a%20moratorium%20on%20new%20licenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Portrait%20of%20Adria%20Berry.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6601cfdb16bde8d4ead1ef7d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAdria%20Berry%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Oklahoma%20Medical%20Marijuana%20Authority%2C%20or%20OMMA%2C%20is%20tasked%20with%20regulating%20and%20tracking%20marijuana%20processing%20and%20selling%20in%20one%20of%20the%20most%20open%20cannabis%20systems%20in%20the%20US.%3Cp%3EMike%20Simons%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAdria%20Berry%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Oklahoma%20Medical%20Marijuana%20Authority%2C%20is%20tempted%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20told%20you%20so.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20personally%20not%20against%20the%20use%20of%20cannabis%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20But%20the%20lack%20of%20any%20regulatory%20framework%20meant%20only%20one%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20obviously%20going%20to%20explode.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20Barb%20Miuccio%2C%20a%2052-year-old%20entrepreneur%20then%20based%20in%20the%20northern%20suburbs%20of%20Dallas%2C%20was%20looking%20for%20business%20opportunities%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20She%20wanted%20a%20new%20business%20%E2%80%94%20one%20she%20could%20potentially%20pass%20on%20to%20her%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20partnered%20with%20Jeremy%20Grable%2C%20an%20experienced%20marijuana%20grower%20looking%20to%20capitalize%20on%20Oklahoma's%20lax%20laws.%20Originally%20from%20Dallas%2C%20Jeremy%20honed%20his%20marijuana-growing%20skills%20out%20West%20before%20returning%20home.%20Considering%20Oklahoma's%20approach%20to%20legal%20weed%2C%20Barb%20and%20Jeremy%20saw%20an%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Barb%20soon%20discovered%20the%20dark%20side%20of%20the%20unchecked%20green%20rush%3A%20minimal%20oversight%2C%20shady%20players%2C%20and%20criminal%20practices.%20After%20years%20of%20thwarted%20harvests%2C%20broken%20partnerships%2C%20and%20the%20very%20real%20threat%20of%20prison%20time%2C%20she%20said%20she's%20burned%20through%20a%20substantial%20amount%20of%20her%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224865%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Portrait%20of%20Barb%20Muccio%20surrounded%20by%20marijuana%20plants.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6601d0b21caec1275a692e3d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223649%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBarbara%20Miuccio%2C%2052%2C%20with%20some%20of%20the%20strains%20of%20marijuana%20grown%20for%20her%20business%2C%20Emerald%20Treez%2C%20in%20Moore%2C%20Oklahoma.%3Cp%3EMike%20Simons%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBarb%2C%20who%20is%20admittedly%20%26quot%3Bnot%20a%20weed%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20saw%20in%20Jeremy%20someone%20with%20a%20green%20thumb%20who%20could%20handle%20the%20plants%20while%20she%20handled%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20meant%20taking%20the%20lead%20on%20licensing.%20But%20Oklahoma%20required%2075%25%20of%20any%20marijuana%20business%20to%20be%20owned%20by%20an%20Oklahoma%20resident.%20A%20quick%20Google%20search%20gave%20her%20options%20for%20plenty%20of%20lawyers%20offering%20to%20help%20would-be%20weed%20entrepreneurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20found%20Matt%20Stacy%2C%20an%20Oklahoma%20City-based%20lawyer%2C%20whose%20background%20seemed%20perfect%20for%20helping%20outsiders%20navigate%20his%20home%20state.%20A%20chummy%2044-year-old%20white%20guy%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20Oklahoma%2C%20Stacy%20served%20for%20over%2020%20years%20in%20Oklahoma's%20Army%20National%20Guard%2C%20where%20he's%20a%20lieutenant%20colonel%20and%20decorated%20war%20hero%20after%20serving%20multiple%20tours%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20Iraq%2C%20and%20Ukraine.%20He's%20a%20member%20of%20numerous%20legal%20associations%20and%20politically%20connected%3A%20Stitt%20appointed%20Stacy%20to%20lead%20the%20state's%20COVID-19%20response%20team%20despite%20Stacy%20having%20no%20evident%20experience%20in%20health%20or%20science%20prior%20to%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224670%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Portrait%20of%20Jeremy%20Grable%20at%20plant%20growing%20facility.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6601d15b3f923f7dab00fd55%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223503%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJeremy%20Grable%2C%2045%2C%20among%20plants%20in%20the%20Moore%2C%20Oklahoma%2C%20building%20where%20he%20grows%20marijuana%20for%20Emerald%20Treez.%20%3Cp%3EMike%20Simons%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBarb%20said%20Stacy%20assured%20them%20he'd%20take%20care%20of%20the%20details%2C%20including%20finding%20an%20Oklahoma%20resident%20to%20claim%20a%2075%25%20stake%20in%20the%20business%2C%20and%20guaranteed%20Barb%20and%20Jeremy%20they'd%20get%20licensed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMatt%20Stacy%20declined%20to%20be%20interviewed%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20August%202020%2C%20Barb%20and%20Jeremy%20had%20Stacy%20on%20retainer%20and%20rented%20a%20beige%2C%20no-frills%20industrial%20building%20in%20Moore%2C%20about%2010%20miles%20south%20of%20Oklahoma%20City.%20Stacy%20told%20them%20that%20he'd%20filed%20their%20paperwork%2C%20and%20in%20September%2C%20inspectors%20from%20OMMA%20dropped%20by%20to%20evaluate%20their%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20all%20happened%20pretty%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20Barb%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarb%20and%20Jeremy%20decided%20on%20a%20name%20%E2%80%94%20Emerald%20Treez%20%E2%80%94%20and%20OMMA%20issued%20them%20a%20license.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20things%20started%20to%20get%20strange.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202020%2C%20according%20to%20Jeremy%20and%20Barb%2C%20Stacy%20called%20them%20out%20of%20the%20blue%20and%20said%20he%20was%20going%20to%20send%20over%20one%20of%20his%20other%20clients%20to%20buy%20marijuana%20plants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20their%20politically%20connected%2C%20Republican%20war-hero%20lawyer%20was%2C%20as%20Barb%20and%20Jeremy%20tell%20it%2C%20acting%20as%20a%20middleman%20didn't%20initially%20strike%20them%20as%20odd.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20like%2C%20'Hey%2C%20this%20guy's%20got%20a%20network%2C'%26quot%3B%20Barb%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarb%20said%20Stacy%20seemed%20to%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20clients%20who%20had%20migrated%20from%20China%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20Oklahoma's%20growing%20laws.%20Jeremy%20and%20Barb%20didn't%20care%20where%20they%20came%20from.%20%26quot%3BMoney's%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Jeremy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20Barbara%20and%20Jeremy%20said%2C%20Stacy%20hooked%20them%20up%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bmarijuana-friendly%26quot%3B%20local%20bank%20%E2%80%94%20a%20necessity%20since%20federally%20backed%20banks%20won't%20accept%20deposits%20for%20marijuana%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20some%20of%20Stacy's%20advice%20about%20banking%20seemed%20off%2C%20like%20telling%20them%20not%20to%20open%20an%20account%20in%20their%20names%20or%20under%20the%20name%20Emerald%20Treez.%20%26quot%3BHe%20told%20us%2C%20'Go%20open%20your%20bank%20account%20in%20this%20name.%20Don't%20tell%20'em%20it's%20marijuana%2C'%26quot%3B%20Barb%20said.%20When%20she%20questioned%20this%2C%20she%20said%20Stacy%20responded%3A%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20don't%20worry.%20I%20walk%20in%20there%20with%20gym%20bags%20full%20of%20half%20a%20million%20dollars%20and%20it's%20all%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20banking%20irregularities%2C%20they%20continued%20working%20with%20Stacy%20%E2%80%94%20he%20had%2C%20after%20all%2C%20fulfilled%20his%20promise%20to%20set%20up%20their%20license%2C%20and%20he%20continued%20to%20send%20them%20clients%20who%20wanted%20to%20buy%20plants.%20They%20assumed%20his%20connections%20in%20the%20state%20would%20protect%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Marijuana%20saplings.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6601d54416bde8d4ead1f622%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20of%20the%20various%20strains%20of%20cannabis%20grown%20at%20Emerald%20Treez.%3Cp%3EMike%20Simons%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202020%2C%20one%20of%20Stacy's%20clients%20visited%20Emerald%20Treez%20to%20buy%20plants%20but%20asked%20to%20see%20their%20OBN%20license%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarb%20said%20it%20was%20the%20first%20time%20she'd%20heard%20of%20the%20Oklahoma%20Bureau%20of%20Narcotics%20and%20Dangerous%20Drugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarijuana%20licensing%20in%20Oklahoma%20was%20lax%20but%20it%20did%20require%20registering%20with%20OBN%20as%20well%20as%20OMMA%2C%20which%20neither%20Barb%20nor%20Jeremy%20knew%20about%20because%2C%20they%20said%2C%20Stacy%20hadn't%20told%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStacy%20blamed%20the%20mix-up%20on%20OBN%2C%20Barb%20said.%20He%20texted%20Barb%20a%20screenshot%20of%20what%20was%20supposedly%20Emerald%20Treez's%20OBN%20license%20number.%20The%20potential%20buyer%20wouldn't%20accept%20it%20because%20it%20wasn't%20an%20OBN%20application%20number%20%E2%80%94%20not%20even%20close.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarb%20and%20Jeremy%20pushed%20ahead%2C%20not%20knowing%20the%20worst%20was%20still%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%20in%20May%202021%2C%20Jeremy%20and%20Barb%20left%20the%20grow%20facility%20to%20get%20supplies.%20According%20to%20Barb%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20a%20neighboring%20building%20called%20Jeremy%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BOBN%20is%20at%20your%20building.%20Doors%20open%20on%20squad%20cars%2C%20guns%20drawn.%26quot%3B%20Their%20neighbor%2C%20Barb%20said%2C%20walked%20over%20and%20the%20agents%20told%20him%20to%20mind%20his%20business.%20Barb%20and%20Jeremy%20decided%20to%20stay%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20OBN%20didn't%20raid%20Barb%20and%20Jeremy's%20business%20then%2C%20but%20they%20called%20Matt%20Stacy%20and%20said%20Stacy%20marked%20it%20up%20to%20confusion%20%E2%80%94%20OBN%20probably%20had%20the%20wrong%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20assumed%20their%20lawyer%20was%20right%20and%20went%20back%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2030%2C%202021%20%E2%80%94%20nearly%20a%20year%20after%20they%20started%20the%20process%20to%20grow%20in%20Oklahoma%20%E2%80%94%20Barb%20and%20Jeremy%20received%20an%20email%20from%20Stacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%2C%20'Your%20grow%20is%20not%20gonna%20get%20approved%20for%20a%20license%2C%20and%20if%20you%20have%20any%20product%20in%20your%20building%2C%20I%20suggest%20you%20get%20rid%20of%20it%20now%2C'%26quot%3B%20Barb%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20tried%20to%20call%20Stacy%20but%20he%20didn't%20pick%20up.%20They%20got%20in%20the%20car%20and%20drove%20to%20Stacy's%20office%2C%20but%20it%20was%20locked%20up%20tight%20with%20no%20one%20inside%3B%20it%20looked%20to%20be%20closed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarb%20and%20Jeremy%20were%20dumbfounded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20losing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Barb%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20chaotic%2C%20unregulated%20gold%20rush%20that%20sucked%20in%20Barb%20and%20Jeremy%20left%20four%20dead%20in%20Kingfisher%20County.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20garage%20where%20three%20men%20and%20one%20woman%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20them%20Chinese%20nationals%20%E2%80%94%20were%20killed%20in%20November%202022%20was%20unlocked%20on%20the%20January%20morning%20when%20Business%20Insider%20visited%20this%20year.%20The%20saltbox-roofed%20building%20was%20a%20refuge%20from%20zero-degree%20temperatures%20and%20cutting%20wind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20heavy%2C%20gray%20metal%20fence%20slid%20open%20on%20creaking%20casters.%20A%20dirt%20path%20led%20to%20the%20building%20where%20the%20killings%20occurred%20%E2%80%94%20the%20garage%20with%20the%20hangers%20and%20the%20blood%20splatter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224873%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Crime%20scene%20with%20blood%20spatter.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6601d1c716bde8d4ead1f116%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223654%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20dried%20bloodstain%20remains%20on%20the%20wall%20of%20a%20garage%20on%20the%20Kingfisher%20County%20marijuana%20farm%20where%20Wu%20Chen%20executed%20four%20people%20on%20November%2020%2C%202022.%20Chen%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20the%20killings%20on%20February%2011.%3Cp%3EMike%20Simons%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20large%20mobile-home%20trailer%20sat%20just%20behind%20the%20garage.%20Inside%20the%20trailer%2C%20a%20sign%20on%20the%20door%20was%20written%20in%20Chinese%3A%20%26quot%3BPlease%20shut%20the%20door%20behind%20you.%26quot%3B%20Clothes%20were%20strewn%20everywhere.%20In%20the%20main%20room%2C%20two%20refrigerators%20sat%20empty%2C%20save%20for%20some%20decaying%20condiment%20bottles.%20Dry%20weed%20shake%20lay%20intermingled%20with%20dust%20on%20the%20floor.%20A%20hallway%20adjacent%20to%20the%20main%20room%20led%20to%20at%20least%20six%20bedrooms%20with%20mattresses%20and%20Chinese%20soda%20and%20beer%20cans%20and%20cigarette%20butts%20on%20the%20floor%20and%20more%20shoes%20and%20clothing%20tossed%20everywhere.%20In%20another%20section%20of%20the%20mobile%20home%2C%20the%20kitchen%20was%20a%20dusty%20jumble%20of%20pots%20and%20pans%20toppled%20over%20in%20haphazard%20piles%20to%20the%20floor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Destroyed%20kitchen.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6601ce9f3f923f7dab00faad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20abandoned%20mobile%20home%20on%20the%20Kingfisher%20County%20farm%20where%20four%20murders%20took%20place.%3Cp%3EMike%20Simons%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJonathan%20Riedlinger%2C%20one%20of%20the%20Kingfisher%20County%20sheriff's%20deputies%20who%20arrived%20at%20the%20scene%20after%20the%20murders%2C%20said%20the%20farm%20itself%20was%20mostly%20empty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverything%20was%20overgrown%2C%26quot%3B%20Riedlinger%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20wasn't%20a%20whole%20lot%20there.%20There%20was%20one%20barn%20that%20had%20two%20rooms%20that%20had%20an%20active%20marijuana%20grow.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20dusk%20on%20November%2020%2C%202022%2C%20Riedlinger's%20office%20received%20an%20emergency%20call%20from%20Yi%20Fei%20Lin%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fs3.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24457727%2Faffidavits-description-of-hostage-situation.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echarging%20documents%3C%2Fa%3E%20filed%20by%20the%20Oklahoma%20State%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation.%20Despite%20a%20language%20barrier%2C%20Lin%20attempted%20to%20describe%20a%20hostage%20situation%20at%202372%20N.%202760%20Road%2C%20in%20Hennessey%2C%20Oklahoma.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESheriff's%20deputies%20arrived%20and%20found%20Lin%20in%20a%20black%20Ford%20F-150.%20He%20had%20been%20shot%20multiple%20times%20and%20was%20severely%20wounded.%20Deputies%20cautiously%20approached%20the%20two-car%20garage%2C%20where%20they%20found%20three%20men%20and%20a%20woman%20%E2%80%94%20later%20identified%20as%20Qirong%20Lin%2C%20Hechun%20Chen%2C%20He%20Qiang%20Chen%2C%20and%20Fang%20Lee%20%E2%80%94%20dead%20on%20the%20garage%20floor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeputies%20found%20two%20other%20people%20alive%20on%20the%20farm.%20One%20survivor%2C%20Wenbo%20Lin%2C%20told%20investigators%20through%20a%20translator%20that%20he%20had%20been%20working%20on%20the%20farm%20for%2010%20days.%20On%20the%20night%20of%20the%20murders%2C%20Wenbo%20Lin%20told%20investigators%20that%20he%20was%20working%20in%20the%20garage%20when%20a%20man%20named%20Wu%20Chen%20%E2%80%94%20whom%20Wenbo%20Lin%20didn't%20know%2C%20but%20another%20witness%20told%20investigators%20Chen%20had%20worked%20on%20the%20farm%20a%20year%20earlier%20%E2%80%94%20arrived%20unannounced.%20Witnesses%20told%20investigators%20that%20once%20inside%20the%20garage%2C%20Chen%20shot%20one%20man%2C%20identified%20as%20%26quot%3BThe%20Boss%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20leg%20and%20then%20shot%20a%20dog.%20Chen%20then%20held%20the%20four%20others%20at%20gunpoint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChen%20demanded%20%24300%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20the%20charging%20documents%2C%20and%20he%20threatened%20to%20kill%20everyone%20in%20the%20room%20if%20he%20didn't%20get%20it.%20Over%20the%20next%20half%20hour%2C%20workers%20at%20the%20farm%20made%20phone%20calls%2C%20desperately%20trying%20to%20pull%20together%20the%20money.%20While%20they%20waited%2C%20two%20of%20the%20men%20in%20the%20garage%20attempted%20to%20rush%20Chen.%20Chen%20shot%20and%20killed%20one%20of%20the%20men%2C%20and%20then%20shot%20Yi%20Fei%20Lin%20as%20he%20attempted%20to%20flee%20the%20garage.%20Lin%20was%20able%20to%20hide%20and%20told%20investigators%20that%20he%20heard%20multiple%20shots%20from%20inside%20the%20garage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225085%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Farm%20house%20under%20investigation.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6602dcb91caec1275a696f1e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223814%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMore%20than%20a%20year%20after%20the%20murders%2C%20the%20property%20remains%20empty.%3Cp%3EMike%20Simons%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20aftermath%2C%20the%20shot%20dog%20whimpered%20beside%20its%20dead%20owner.%20%26quot%3BShe%20wasn't%20aggressive%2C%26quot%3B%20Riedlinger%20said%20of%20the%20dog.%20%26quot%3BI%20mean%2C%20she%20was%20pretty%20docile%20for%20being%20shot.%20You%20would've%20thought%20that%20she'd%20be%20a%20little%20more%20mad.%26quot%3B%20A%20vet%20came%20and%20checked%20the%20dog%20out%2C%20but%20Reidlinger%20didn't%20know%20what%20happened%20to%20the%20dog%20after%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Kingfisher%20murders%20were%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20Oklahoma's%20marijuana%20crackdown.%20%26quot%3BIt%20woke%20the%20public%20up%2C%20it%20scared%20the%20public%20because%20they're%20all%20over%20Oklahoma%20%E2%80%94%20these%20farms%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20Mark%20Woodward%2C%20from%20the%20OBN%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20people%20started%20saying%2C%20'That%20could%20happen%20across%20the%20road%20from%20me%20and%20my%20family.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJed%20Green%2C%20a%20pro-marijuana%20activist%20in%20Oklahoma%2C%20said%20the%20murders%20%26quot%3Breinforced%20the%20narrative%20that%20the%20majority%20%E2%80%94%20or%20at%20least%20a%20lot%20%E2%80%94%20of%20the%20grow%20operations%20here%20are%20or%20have%20been%20operated%20by%20cartels.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20one%20thing%20to%20bust%20some%20folks%20and%20say%2C%20'Hey%2C%20this%20was%20a%20cartel%20deal%2C'%26quot%3B%20Green%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20when%20you%20have%20a%20quadruple%20homicide%2C%20it%20really%20drives%20home%20the%20narrative%20point%20of%20the%20shady%20criminal%20side%20of%20a%20number%20of%20these%20past%20operations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225015%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22County%20court%20house.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6601d7d91caec1275a693b3f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223761%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDeputies%20from%20the%20Kingfisher%20County%20Sheriff's%20Office%20were%20the%20first%20to%20arrive%20at%20the%20scene%20of%20a%20quadruple%20homicide%20at%20an%20abandoned%20marijuana%20farm.%3Cp%3EMike%20Simons%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2017%2C%202022%2C%20Oklahoma%20prosecutors%20filed%2034%20felony%20charges%20against%20Matthew%20Alan%20Stacy%2C%20including%20five%20counts%20of%20illegally%20manufacturing%20thousands%20of%20pounds%20of%20marijuana%20%E2%80%94%20charges%20that%2C%20if%20he%20were%20convicted%2C%20could%20put%20Stacy%20in%20prison%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20life%20and%20then%20some.%20Barb%20and%20Jeremy%20are%20listed%20as%20witnesses%20in%20the%20charging%20documents.%20Stacy%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20to%20the%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20of%20Oklahoma%20isn't%20claiming%20that%20Stacy%20grew%20pot%20illegally%20in%20some%20back%20room%20of%20his%20law%20office.%20It%20alleges%20that%20he%20led%20at%20least%20six%20aspiring%20growers%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Jeremy%20and%20Barb%20%E2%80%94%20to%20believe%20that%20they%20had%20submitted%20all%20the%20necessary%20paperwork%20to%20be%20licensed%20to%20grow%20pot%20under%20Oklahoma's%20new%20rules%20when%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20they%20hadn't.%20Prosecutors%20say%20that%20since%20Stacy%20led%20the%20growers%20to%20believe%20they%20could%20legally%20manufacture%20a%20controlled%20substance%20%E2%80%94%20literally%20thousands%20of%20pounds%20of%20marijuana%20%E2%80%94%20he's%20ultimately%20responsible%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStacy%20also%20set%20up%20a%20network%20of%20%26quot%3Bstraw%20owners%2C%26quot%3B%20prosecutors%20say%2C%20helping%20out-of-state%20growers%20skirt%20the%20requirement%20that%2075%25%20of%20a%20cannabis%20business%20be%20owned%20by%20Oklahoma%20residents.%20He%20was%20listed%20as%20the%20registered%20agent%20for%20at%20least%20214%20different%20LLCs%20licensed%20to%20grow%20or%20sell%20marijuana%20through%20OMMA.%20He'd%20put%20his%20own%20name%20on%20these%20license%20applications%2C%20prosecutors%20say%2C%20and%20then%20used%20names%20of%20other%20Oklahoma%20residents%20to%20ensure%20that%20each%20application%20technically%20met%20threshold%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStraw%20owners%20would%20claim%20to%20own%2075%25%20of%20a%20business%20while%20knowing%20almost%20nothing%20about%20it.%20%26quot%3BThese%20people%20said%2C%20'All%20I%20know%20about%20the%20business%20is%20that%20I%20go%20to%20the%20mailbox%20once%20a%20month%2C%20and%20I%20get%20a%20check%20to%20say%20that%20I'm%20the%20owner%2C'%26quot%3B%20Woodward%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20committed%20fraud.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20Stacy's%20preliminary%20hearing%20in%20May%202023%2C%20a%20woman%20named%20Helen%20Carillo%2C%20the%20Oklahoma%20resident%20listed%20on%20Barb%20and%20Jeremey's%20application%2C%20testified%20that%20Stacy%20had%20paid%20her%20%245%2C000%20apiece%20to%20be%20a%20silent%20owner%20for%20three%20marijuana%20licenses%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20placed%20her%20name%20on%20dozens%20of%20others%20without%20informing%20her.%20Her%20objection%20was%20not%20that%20Stacy%20placed%20her%20name%20on%20dozens%20of%20licenses%20but%20that%20she%20didn't%20get%20paid%20for%20all%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarb%20and%20Jeremy%20are%20also%20suing%20Stacy%20in%20civil%20court.%20The%20case%20is%20pending%2C%20and%20Stacy%20has%20filed%20a%20motion%20to%20dismiss%20the%20allegations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe's%20personally%20responsible%20for%20ruining%20our%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Jeremy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20the%20state%20charges%20against%20Stacy%20indicate%20a%20connection%20to%20violent%20crimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20abandoned%20marijuana%20farm%20in%20Kingfisher%20County%20was%20also%20licensed%20with%20a%20straw%20owner.%20The%20person%20who%20arranged%20that%20license%20%E2%80%94%20Kevin%20Pham%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20CSI%20Accounting%20Services%20in%20Oklahoma%20City%20%E2%80%94%20is%20charged%20with%20many%20of%20the%20same%20crimes%20Stacy%20faces%2C%20including%20defrauding%20the%20state%20by%20providing%20false%20information%20to%20obtain%20marijuana%20licenses.%20(Pham%20also%20faces%20methamphetamine%20trafficking%20and%20firearms%20charges.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224523%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kevin%20Pham%20in%20court%20house.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6601d2ea1caec1275a69321f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223392%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKevin%20Pham%2C%2047%2C%20covering%20his%20face%20at%20a%20January%2012%20hearing%20in%20Kingfisher%20County.%20Pham%20has%20been%20charged%20by%20Oklahoma%20prosecutors%20with%20defrauding%20the%20state%20by%20providing%20false%20information%20to%20obtain%20marijuana%20growing%20licenses%2C%20including%20the%20one%20for%20the%20farm%20where%20Wu%20Chen%20murdered%20four%20people.%3Cp%3EMike%20Simons%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPham%20has%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20in%20the%20ongoing%20case.%20He%20declined%20to%20speak%20to%20Business%20Insider%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOklahoma's%20primary%20illegal-drug%20law-enforcement%20entity%20has%20shut%20down%20thousands%20of%20marijuana-growing%20operations%2C%20arrested%20more%20than%20250%20people%20connected%20with%20those%20grows%2C%20and%20confiscated%20nearly%201%20million%20pounds%20of%20illegally%20grown%20marijuana%2C%20according%20to%20internal%20OBN%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20are%20grows%20that%20are%20tied%20to%20homicide%2C%20that%20are%20tied%20to%20sex%20trafficking%20and%20labor%20trafficking%20and%20environmental%20messes%2C%20gambling%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20Woodward%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20talking%20about%20nearly%2011%2C000%20businesses%20that%20were%20operating%20in%20Oklahoma.%26quot%3B%20OBN's%20job%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20to%20figure%20out%20who%20was%20doing%20it%20legally%20versus%20illegally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202022%20report%20from%20Whitney%20Economics%2C%20a%20group%20that%20studies%20the%20cannabis%20industry%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubscriber.politicopro.com%2Farticle%2F2022%2F12%2Freport-75-percent-of-u-s-cannabis-market-is-illicit-sales-00072206%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20as%20much%20as%2075%20percent%20of%20marijuana%20production%20in%20the%20US%20is%20done%20for%20unlawful%20sales.%20An%20investigation%20by%20ProPublica%20and%20The%20Frontier%20uncovered%20evidence%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpropublica.org%2Farticle%2Fchinese-organized-crime-us-marijuana-market%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20organized%20crime%3C%2Fa%3E%20groups%20engaging%20in%20human%20trafficking%20to%20support%20illicit%20marijuana%20operations.%20NBC%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbc.com%2Fnightly-news-films%2Fvideo%2Fcaptives-of-cannabis-human-trafficking-in-the-marijuana-industry-part-2%2FNBCN606981904%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espoke%20to%20Chinese%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20illegal%20grows%20in%20California%20who%20said%20they%20were%20recruited%20for%20their%20jobs%20through%20Mandarin-language%20websites%2C%20and%20a%20Searchlight%20New%20Mexico%20investigation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsearchlightnm.org%2Ffields-of-green%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Mandarin-language%20ads%20run%20on%20the%20social-media%20app%20WeChat%20offered%20to%20bring%20Chinese%20nationals%20Stateside%20to%20work%20on%20illegal%20farms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWoodward%20said%20Oklahoma%20is%20ground%20zero%20for%20these%20workers%20and%20illegal%20marijuana%20production%20generally.%20Court%20filings%20in%20Oklahoma%20seem%20to%20back%20up%20that%20belief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202023%2C%20local%20law%20enforcement%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.koco.com%2Farticle%2Foklahoma-city-amazon-van-marijuana-bust%2F43558431%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earrested%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20Chinese%20national%20and%20accused%20him%20of%20transporting%20more%20than%202%2C700%20pounds%20of%20marijuana%20in%20a%20fake%20Amazon%20delivery%20truck%20to%20an%20Oklahoma%20City%20grow%20operation%20for%20illegal%20distribution.%20Another%20raid%20led%20to%20charges%20against%20owners%20of%20a%20Chinese%20restaurant%2C%20who%20prosecutors%20say%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.koco.com%2Farticle%2Foklahoma-city-restaurant-the-kitchen-federal-money-laundering-drug-scheme%2F43902717%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econcocted%20a%20scheme%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20launder%20%2425%20million%20in%20illegal%20marijuana%20proceeds.%20In%20January%2C%20local%20police%20raided%20an%20Airbnb%20in%20Edmond%2C%20just%20north%20of%20Oklahoma%20City%2C%20and%20arrested%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.news9.com%2Fstory%2F65a847de5e0a905bd8199944%2F9-arrested-charged-with-drug-trafficking-in-edmond-rental-house%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enine%20Chinese%20nationals%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20are%20facing%20charges%20related%20to%20distributing%20marijuana%20out%20of%20state.%20And%20human%20trafficking%20is%20a%20constant%20concern%3A%20In%20October%2C%20investigators%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fokcfox.com%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Foklahoma-city-trafficking-ring-brothel-oklahoma-bureau-of-narcotics-jian-lin-feng-jeng-mark-woodward-new-york-city-prostitution%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earrested%20a%20suspect%20%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20human-trafficking%20charges%2C%20alleging%20he%20was%20involved%20in%20an%20Oklahoma%20City%20brothel%20where%20many%20clients%20appeared%20to%20be%20managers%20and%20administrators%20of%20Chinese-owned%20marijuana%20grows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWoodward%20said%20one%20of%20OBN's%20goals%20is%20to%20help%20legitimate%20growers%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20industry%20just%20has%20not%20had%20a%20chance%20to%20even%20really%20get%20off%20the%20ground%20because%20the%20criminals%20immediately%20came%20in%20and%20undercut%20prices%20and%20workers%20and%20labor%20costs%20and%20everything.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Oklahoma's%20marijuana%20crackdown%20has%20sparked%20accusations%20%E2%80%94%20perhaps%20not%20surprisingly%2C%20given%20the%20xenophobic%20overtones%20%E2%80%94%20of%20overreach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Vietnamese%20Hmong%20grower%20near%20Tulsa%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20and%20other%20Hmong%20growers%20are%20targeted%20by%20OBN%20and%20local%20law%20enforcement%20as%20though%20they're%20on%20orders%20from%20China%20to%20grow%20marijuana%20and%20ship%20it%20illegally%20to%20other%20states.%20They%20%26quot%3Bsee%20all%20Asians%20as%20Chinese%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20The%20grower%2C%20a%20former%20schoolteacher%2C%20declined%20to%20be%20identified%2C%20fearing%20recriminations%20for%20speaking%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOBN%20denied%20it%20targeted%20Asian%20growers.%20%26quot%3BOBN%20has%20identified%20and%20shut%20down%20illegal%20grows%2C%20as%20well%20as%20made%20arrests%20on%20illegal%20farms%20tied%20to%20organized%20crime%20from%20China%2C%20Mexico%2C%20Russia%2C%20Bulgaria%2C%20Armenia%2C%20and%20the%20Italian%20mob%20over%20the%20last%20three%20years%2C%20as%20well%20as%20numerous%20American-owned%20and%20operated%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Woodward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreen%2C%20the%20legal-weed%20advocate%20who%20heads%20up%20Oklahomans%20for%20Responsible%20Cannabis%20Action%2C%20described%20the%20rocky%20start%20in%20Oklahoma's%20legalization%20efforts%20as%20growing%20pains.%20He%20talked%20about%20the%20historical%20booms%20and%20busts%20of%20Oklahoma%20industries%20like%20oil%2C%20shale%20gas%2C%20and%20wheat%2C%20which%20contributed%20to%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20environmental%20disasters%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Dust%20Bowl%20%E2%80%94%20in%20American%20history.%20Oklahoma's%20aggressive%20law-enforcement%20efforts%20to%20eliminate%20marijuana%20grows%20are%20typical%20for%20the%20state.%20%26quot%3BYou%20get%20a%20rush%20of%20enthusiasm%2C%20then%20a%20clampdown%2C%26quot%3B%20Green%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreen%20sees%20Oklahoma's%20marijuana%20troubles%20as%20a%20hiccup%20in%20the%20gradual%20movement%20toward%20federal%20legalization.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20our%20goal%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20it's%20difficult%20to%20imagine%20Oklahoma's%20half-decade%20weed%20rollout%20being%20as%20chaotic%20as%20it%20has%20been%20if%20Congress%20passed%20federal%20legislation%20making%20marijuana%20legal%20and%20regulating%20it%20like%20alcohol%20%E2%80%94%20with%20federal%20rules%20around%20production%20but%20allowing%20each%20state%20to%20make%20its%20own%20rules%20around%20sale%20and%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarb%20and%20Jeremy%20have%20an%20interest%20in%20seeing%20marijuana%20legalized%20at%20the%20federal%20level%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20a%20rough%20few%20years%20for%20them.%20They%20were%20forced%20to%20destroy%20a%20crop%20because%20of%20OBN%20licensing%20issues%2C%20and%20then%20their%20grow%20operation%20caught%20fire%2C%20apparently%20because%20of%20faulty%20electrical%20work%2C%20killing%20a%20harvest.%20They%20tried%20to%20open%20a%20dispensary%20to%20sell%20their%20product%2C%20but%20the%20deal%20they%20were%20working%20on%20went%20sour.%20They%20hope%20to%20sell%20through%20other%20dispensaries%20when%20their%20current%20harvest%20is%20ready%20for%20sale%2C%20but%20so%20far%20Emerald%20Treez%20is%20deep%20in%20the%20red.%20Barb's%20hope%20is%20that%20if%20marijuana%20does%20become%20legal%20on%20a%20federal%20level%2C%20they%20can%20expand%20their%20business%20out%20of%20Oklahoma.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20then%2C%20they're%20stuck%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20steak%20dinner%20at%20Cattlemen's%20Steakhouse%20in%20Oklahoma%20City%20in%20February%2C%20Barb%20considered%20whether%20she%20would%20have%20done%20things%20differently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20I'll%20tell%20you%20what%20I%20wish%20I%20did%20differently%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20taking%20a%20drag%20off%20a%20Virginia%20Slim.%20%26quot%3BI%20wish%20I'd%20never%20fucking%20stepped%20foot%20in%20Oklahoma.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225163%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22House%20of%20the%20murder%20occurrence.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6601d47d1caec1275a6935c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223872%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20deserted%20farm%20in%20Kingfisher%20County.%3Cp%3EMike%20Simons%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20murders%2C%20Wu%20Chen%20fled%20the%20scene%2C%20but%20he%20dropped%20his%20phone.%20Investigators%20were%20able%20to%20analyze%20it%20and%20determined%20he%20was%20headed%20to%20Florida.%20Police%20in%20Miami%20Beach%20found%20him%20two%20days%20later%2C%20on%20November%2022%2C%202022%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fnews%2Fus-news%2F4-people-found-dead-oklahoma-marijuana-farm-chinese-nationals-executed-rcna58463%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earrested%20him%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKen%20Thompson%2C%20a%20Kingfisher%20County%20Sheriff's%20Office%20lieutenant%20deputy%2C%20traveled%20to%20Miami%20with%20another%20deputy%20to%20drive%20Chen%20back.%20Thompson%20said%20Chen%20didn't%20speak%20a%20word%20of%20English.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20like%20he%20could%20tell%20me%20anything%20about%20his%20concerns%2C%26quot%3B%20Thompson%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20gathered%20he%20feared%20for%20his%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestigators%20said%20Chen%20told%20them%20through%20translators%20that%20he'd%20invested%20%24300%2C000%20in%20the%20farm%20and%20came%20to%20get%20it%20back.%20The%20farm's%20owner%20was%20unable%20to%20come%20up%20with%20the%20money%20to%20pay%20Chen.%20At%20some%20point%2C%20he%20opened%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20rumors%20around%20the%20Kingfisher%20County%20courthouse%20that%20the%20killings%20may%20have%20been%20in%20retaliation%20for%20another%20shooting.%20Court%20records%20showed%20Yi%20Fe